  luciferRemark: 'Ah, pride. My favorite sin.

    

    (Pause.)

    

    He
    never imagined he could fail. Meticulous planning. Perfect timing. An airtight
    alibi. The only thing he didn''t account for was a heart too excited to keep
    beating.

    

    (Low chuckle.)

    

    What was he thinking when he
    died? The insurance payout? His new life? Or the people he set ablaze?

    

    The
    answer is: none of them.

    

    When he died, he was thinking - ''I won.'''
